2002.assessment:
GDP per capita ~$2,201. Growth accelerating (~5% real). China demand driving
commodity prices; Peru's copper, zinc, gold benefiting. Democracy restored;
investment sentiment improving. Beginning of sustained growth phase through 2013.

2008.assessment:
Trade openness ~51%. Highest level. Commodity price peak drove export values;
import of capital goods and consumption goods very high with 9.8% growth.
Peru FTA with US entered into force February 2009. Strong trade integration.
